    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/3–148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Batavia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-01">March 1,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. <gloss target="#t_Usgoc1">Usgoc</gloss> 71. Following resolutions proposed by
                    Canada (Document S/678) and China (Document S/P.V. 259) respectively, were
                    adopted by <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> at its 259th meeting, 28 Feb
                        1948:<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1">See <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi
                            rend="italic">3rd yr</hi>., nos. 16–35, pp. 367, 380, 381, 393.</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item> “<hi rend="smallcaps">The Security Council</hi>, <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >having</hi> considered the Report of the Committee of Good Offices,
                            informing the Council of the steps taken by the Netherlands Government
                            and the Government of the Republic of Indonesia to comply with the
                            Council’s resolution of 1 August 1947;</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Notes</hi> with satisfaction the signing of the
                            Truce Agreement by both parties and the acceptance by both parties of
                            certain principles as an agreed basis for the conclusion of a political
                            settlement in Indonesia;</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Commends</hi> the members of the Committee of Good
                            Offices for the assistance they have given the two parties in their
                            endeavours to settle their dispute by peaceful means;</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Maintains</hi> its offer of good offices contained
                            in the resolution of 25 August 1947, and, to this end,</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Requests</hi> both parties and the Committee of
                            Good Offices to keep the Council directly informed about the progress of
                            the political settlement in Indonesia.”</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>“The Security Council requests the Committee of Good Offices to pay
                            particular attention to the political development in Western Java and
                            Madura and to report to the Council thereon at frequent
                            intervals.”</item>
                    </list>
                </quote>
                <p>(Repeated to The Hague as 75).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
